### Relevant Information:

**Event Title:** COM - V.E.N.D. at SAINTCON

**Date:** October 2024

**Organizer:** bashNinja

**Event Description:**
- The V.E.N.D. Machine offers customizable virtual environments for hacking, learning, and exploring during SAINTCON.
- Attendees can access and deploy a variety of virtual machines (VMs) such as:
  - Windows 11
  - Kali Linux
  - Ubuntu
  - Debian
  - BlackArch
  - Arch
  - Parrot Linux

**Features of the V.E.N.D. Machine:**
- **Location & Availability:** Available at a central spot within the SAINTCON conference from the first to the last day during regular hours.
- **Deployment Process:** Attendees select their desired VM and are guided through the setup via the machine interface. 
- **Access Method:** A receipt with login credentials is printed for remote access to the VM.
- **Customization:** Attendees can install necessary tools and applications on the VM for the duration of the conference.

**Benefits:**
- Variety of environments available, catering to different experience levels.
- Hands-on learning opportunities for skills practiced in workshops or talks.

**FAQs:**
- **Can I share my VM?** Yes, scripts for sharing are provided.
- **Can I save work on the VM?** No, all VMs will be decommissioned post-conference.
- **Restrictions on installations?** Illegal activities and harmful software are prohibited per the SAINTCON Code of Conduct.
- **Technical issues support:** Available during the conference via a dedicated support team.
- **Cost:** Free to use.
- **Self-hosting:** Guides will be shared on how to operate VM/Container setups closer to the conference.

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Monday:** Closed
- **Tuesday:** Noon – 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday:** 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Thursday:** 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Friday:** 9:00 AM – 11:00 AM

**Community Engagement:**
- The event features various communities, allowing networking and collaboration.

This content captures the essence of the V.E.N.D. Machine, the experience it offers at SAINTCON, and relevant operational details for attendees.